        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-07-01T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-07-01T16:00:00-05:00" n="104"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d104">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">741.94/111: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="47" xml:id="d104fn47">Repeated as No. 104 to the Embassy in
                        China.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-07-01T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 1, 1937—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>102. Department’s No. 94, June 24, 5 p.m. Under date June 30 the Embassy at
                    London telegraphs as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Cadogan informed me that Yoshida had as yet made no request for
                            appointment to present any memorandum in spite of press reports from
                            Tokyo.</p>
                        <p>Cadogan said he felt Japanese position has stiffened since Hirota had
                            taken office and if there were any truth in rumors coming from Tokyo
                            that in negotiations with His Majesty’s Government Japan would be
                            disposed to merely redefine her position as to ‘special régimes’ in
                            North China and ‘special trade’ in that area, he was not hopeful of the
                            outcome.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
